%N A396688 Last term of an n X n generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of primes with smallest last term.
%C A396688 The n X n generalized arithmetic progression (GAP) of distinct primes with smallest last term is of the form a+b*i+c*j, with 0 <= i,j <= n-1.
%C A396688 See A391764 a-file for details on equations and terms.
%e A396688 Table detailing the n X n GAPs, with 2 <= n <= 5:
%e A396688   n  GAP                       Last term
%e A396688   2  3+8*i+2*j                 13
%e A396688   3  29+12*i+30*j              113
%e A396688   4  503+360*i+1218*j          5237
%e A396688   5  219767+145860*i+768810*j  3878447
